<h4 id="drive-guide---greentop---to-knoxville">Drive Guide - Greentop - TO Knoxville</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Directions</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li>Head downhill (sharp L from tower driveway) and go 1.0</li>
      <li>Sharp R ond Bluff Mtn Rd and go 4.1</li>
      <li>L on Goose Gap Rd and go 4.4</li>
      <li>L on Whites School Rd and go 0.6</li>
      <li>L on US-441 N</li>
      <li>If going to Alcoa Hwy go 13.4
        <ul>
          <li>R on ramp to TN-168 (John Sevier Hwy)</li>
          <li>L on TN-168 W and go 6.7</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>If going to Atlanta, go 20.2 to ramp to I-40 W</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h4 id="trail-guide">Trail Guide</h4>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Duration</strong>: 20 minutes</li>
  <li><strong>Navigation</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>It is a big activation zone.  Coming up the road from Horse Cove Rd, once you round the bend to the left, you are in the zone.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Summit altitude</strong>: 3069’</li>
  <li><strong>GPS tracks/waypoints</strong>: Official Summit: 35.8119, -83.6672</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="summit-guide">Summit Guide</h4>

<ul>
  <li>Hang antenna from tree: No</li>
  <li>Space to guy mast: No</li>
  <li>Cell coverage: AT&amp;T (VZN and APRS not tested)</li>
  <li>Unique features: Summit is full of towers and power lines.  The only wire antenna I could fit was to run a near-vertical sloper off the side of the fire tower or to throw a line over a tree in the “corner” (above poison ivy).  Any place else near the summit was just too close to a power line or an air conditioning noise source.</li>
</ul>
